1
00:00:32,762 --> 00:00:34,518
♪ ♪

2
00:00:34,681 --> 00:00:36,599
[horns honking]

3
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,503
[snoring]

4
00:00:50,793 --> 00:00:52,596
[fan creaking rhythmically]

5
00:00:57,555 --> 00:00:59,645
[train rattling]

6
00:01:07,902 --> 00:01:08,925
- [camera beeps, clicks]
- Years from now,

7
00:01:08,947 --> 00:01:10,156
when you look at this photo,

8
00:01:10,329 --> 00:01:12,420
you'll feel the sun
on your face...

9
00:01:12,582 --> 00:01:13,542
[camera beeps, clicks]

10
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:15,172
<i>...this wind in your hair</i>

11
00:01:15,335 --> 00:01:17,714
<i>and hear
all these voices again.</i>

12
00:01:17,886 --> 00:01:21,098
<i>Or it'll all be gone.
Gone forever.</i>

13
00:01:22,681 --> 00:01:23,765
[camera clicks]

14
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,654
Taking pictures?

15
00:01:25,808 --> 00:01:27,389
That is one of mine up there.

16
00:01:27,562 --> 00:01:29,356
What do you mean?

17
00:01:29,529 --> 00:01:31,034
Your son must be a genius!

18
00:01:31,197 --> 00:01:33,787
Not my son.
I have two daughters.

19
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:36,031
There, in the middle.

20
00:01:36,203 --> 00:01:38,956
That's my younger one, Miloni.

21
00:01:39,129 --> 00:01:40,922
Really?

22
00:01:41,086 --> 00:01:42,256
The one with the crown?

23
00:01:42,428 --> 00:01:44,096
Correct.

24
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:45,780
She finished first
in the CA Foundation exam.

25
00:01:45,804 --> 00:01:48,058
Now she's preparing
for the CA Inter.

26
00:01:48,230 --> 00:01:50,782
My son tried for CA as well.

27
00:01:50,934 --> 00:01:54,569
But now he's going to America
to do his MBA.

28
00:01:56,152 --> 00:01:57,734
Hmm.
[clicks tongue]

29
00:01:57,906 --> 00:02:00,036
No, not this.

30
00:02:00,208 --> 00:02:01,791
Something doesn't look right.

31
00:02:02,999 --> 00:02:04,082
A moment.

32
00:02:04,255 --> 00:02:05,550
Try pink.

33
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:08,513
Look, Miloni!

34
00:02:08,677 --> 00:02:11,093
This looks so good on you.

35
00:02:12,896 --> 00:02:14,527
Ah.
[clicks tongue]

36
00:02:14,690 --> 00:02:16,321
Mum's taste is the best!

37
00:02:16,484 --> 00:02:18,574
That's why I always shop
with her!

38
00:02:19,821 --> 00:02:21,691
Go with pink, I'm telling you.

39
00:02:22,621 --> 00:02:23,877
Hmm?

40
00:02:24,041 --> 00:02:26,505
So... is pink final?

41
00:02:28,174 --> 00:02:29,718
Yes.

42
00:02:29,881 --> 00:02:31,089
Okay.

43
00:02:31,262 --> 00:02:33,554
Let's go, Fazlu bhai.
Pink is final.

44
00:02:33,717 --> 00:02:35,425
Now give us a good price.

45
00:02:35,596 --> 00:02:37,640
No advance payment.

46
00:02:37,812 --> 00:02:41,486
Payment only upon delivery.
We're not stupid.

47
00:02:41,649 --> 00:02:43,604
- [quiet chatter]
- [ship horn honks]

48
00:02:49,042 --> 00:02:50,837
♪ ♪

49
00:03:10,161 --> 00:03:12,003
♪ ♪

50
00:03:33,657 --> 00:03:35,451
[quiet chatter]

51
00:03:39,086 --> 00:03:41,262
Hey. Excuse me.

52
00:03:57,825 --> 00:03:59,657
♪ ♪

53
00:04:18,943 --> 00:04:20,775
♪ ♪

54
00:04:24,832 --> 00:04:26,423
[camera clicking]

55
00:04:33,425 --> 00:04:34,546
Photograph, madam?

56
00:04:36,187 --> 00:04:37,856
With the Gateway or the Taj,
madam.

57
00:04:38,019 --> 00:04:39,265
Instant.

58
00:04:41,605 --> 00:04:44,818
Years from now,
when you look at this photo,

59
00:04:44,991 --> 00:04:48,500
you'll feel the sun
on your face,

60
00:04:48,664 --> 00:04:50,419
this wind in your hair

61
00:04:50,582 --> 00:04:54,629
and hear
all these voices again.

62
00:04:54,802 --> 00:04:56,720
Or it'll all be gone.

63
00:04:56,882 --> 00:04:59,635
Gone forever.

64
00:04:59,808 --> 00:05:01,352
50 rupees.

65
00:05:03,731 --> 00:05:04,977
For you, 30.

66
00:05:08,986 --> 00:05:10,032
Okay.

67
00:05:15,546 --> 00:05:17,300
A bit to the right.

68
00:05:17,464 --> 00:05:19,516
A bit more.

69
00:05:21,971 --> 00:05:24,934
Madam, one paisa of a smile,
please.

70
00:05:25,098 --> 00:05:26,729
Just a paisa.

71
00:05:26,901 --> 00:05:29,068
[camera beeping and clicking]

72
00:05:49,188 --> 00:05:51,107
[printer whirring]

73
00:06:04,045 --> 00:06:05,714
Here, this day in a photograph.

74
00:06:08,552 --> 00:06:10,595
Let me put today
in an envelope for you.

75
00:06:11,851 --> 00:06:13,520
Miloni!

76
00:06:13,683 --> 00:06:15,266
Hey, Miloni!

77
00:06:15,438 --> 00:06:16,896
Miloni!

78
00:06:30,629 --> 00:06:31,712
Rafi!

79
00:06:33,679 --> 00:06:35,511
Rafi!

80
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:38,608
How's business?

81
00:06:48,496 --> 00:06:50,750
This girl,
she had me take a photo.

82
00:06:50,923 --> 00:06:53,388
I was looking for the envelope
and she ran off.

83
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:55,679
- Ran off?
- Ran off.

84
00:06:55,843 --> 00:06:58,010
She pulled the wool
over your eyes.

85
00:06:58,182 --> 00:07:00,024
She'll be in Dadar by now.

86
00:07:01,357 --> 00:07:02,440
Rafi bhai,

87
00:07:02,603 --> 00:07:04,147
I called the village yesterday.

88
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:06,996
Your grandmother was in
our village asking about girls.

89
00:07:08,281 --> 00:07:10,237
My aunt has four.

90
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:12,089
Your aunt with the mustache?

91
00:07:12,241 --> 00:07:16,040
Yes, but the girls
don't have mustaches.

92
00:07:16,213 --> 00:07:18,553
- You marry them, then.
- No, not me!

93
00:07:18,715 --> 00:07:20,759
Your body has amassed
all this anger.

94
00:07:20,931 --> 00:07:22,724
Your grandmother
is right to worry.

95
00:07:22,887 --> 00:07:26,138
She said she'd pay a dowry
for you if she had the money.

96
00:07:26,311 --> 00:07:27,433
What do you say?

97
00:07:29,447 --> 00:07:31,202
What should I say?

98
00:07:31,366 --> 00:07:33,120
If you get married,
at least you'll have

99
00:07:33,284 --> 00:07:34,540
a warm body next to you
at night.

100
00:07:34,703 --> 00:07:36,956
You can go to the zoo
with the kids,

101
00:07:37,119 --> 00:07:39,834
an evening out with the wife...

102
00:07:40,007 --> 00:07:41,339
Yeah, right.

103
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:43,008
The wife and kids will be
in the village

104
00:07:43,171 --> 00:07:46,010
while I'll be stuck here
pining for them.

105
00:07:46,183 --> 00:07:48,811
- You don't do it, either.
- Why not?

106
00:07:48,973 --> 00:07:52,474
You'd become a softie,
like Zakir bhai.

107
00:07:52,647 --> 00:07:54,401
Softie?

108
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:57,288
- What's a softie?
- Never eaten a softie?

109
00:07:58,573 --> 00:08:00,030
A softie is like ice cream.

110
00:08:00,203 --> 00:08:02,783
Like kulfi, but not as hard.

111
00:08:02,956 --> 00:08:07,090
It's so soft,
it melts in your mouth.

112
00:08:07,263 --> 00:08:09,017
Softie.

113
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:12,479
It melts in your mouth?
So what use is it, madam?

114
00:08:12,642 --> 00:08:14,810
That's what I'm saying!

115
00:08:14,983 --> 00:08:17,159
How much do you need to send
home this month, Rafi bhai?

116
00:08:17,323 --> 00:08:18,579
All of it, madam.

117
00:08:21,245 --> 00:08:23,038
Here. This, too.

118
00:08:24,794 --> 00:08:27,171
Keep something for yourself,
too, Rafi miyan.

119
00:08:28,668 --> 00:08:31,133
Want a kulfi?

120
00:08:31,295 --> 00:08:33,886
Why do you always eat kulfi
only at the end of the month?

121
00:08:34,058 --> 00:08:36,772
- My father, when he was alive...
- Hey, Rafi miyan!

122
00:08:37,932 --> 00:08:39,850
What's this I hear?

123
00:08:40,023 --> 00:08:42,229
Your grandmother stopped taking
her medicine?

124
00:08:42,402 --> 00:08:43,859
Because you won't select
a bride?

125
00:08:44,990 --> 00:08:46,544
Where did you hear that, uncle?

126
00:08:46,698 --> 00:08:49,326
His grandmother was asking
around my wife's village.

127
00:08:51,589 --> 00:08:54,217
What kind of girl do you want?
You've never told me.

128
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:58,800
Well, you should've told me!

129
00:09:04,104 --> 00:09:05,063
Look at that.

130
00:09:07,365 --> 00:09:09,082
No one appreciates help
these days...

131
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:15,162
[horn honking]

132
00:09:15,334 --> 00:09:17,129
[food sizzling]

133
00:09:19,555 --> 00:09:20,887
Two kulfis.

134
00:09:24,599 --> 00:09:27,687
Rafi miyan, has Grandma really
stopped taking her medicine?

135
00:09:31,235 --> 00:09:32,779
It's high time you got married.

136
00:09:35,705 --> 00:09:36,798
Rafi miyan?

137
00:09:38,371 --> 00:09:41,669
Is it true what I heard
about your grandma?

138
00:09:41,842 --> 00:09:44,930
And then Rafi throws the kulfi

139
00:09:45,094 --> 00:09:47,348
right in his face.

140
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,486
[laughter]

141
00:09:49,649 --> 00:09:51,030
Then he says,

142
00:09:51,193 --> 00:09:55,662
"I heard you like sweets,

143
00:09:55,826 --> 00:09:58,578
son of a bitch!"

144
00:09:58,742 --> 00:09:59,988
Rafi bhai,

145
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:03,000
if a boat isn't anchored
at the right time,

146
00:10:03,172 --> 00:10:05,463
- it can sink.
- [laughter]

147
00:10:05,627 --> 00:10:09,089
Absolutely, Rafi.
100%, you'll sink!

148
00:10:11,429 --> 00:10:14,018
- He wants you to drown!
- Let me tell you something.

149
00:10:14,191 --> 00:10:16,905
Remember what I told you
about Tiwari?

150
00:10:17,069 --> 00:10:18,254
Zakir bhai,
not that story again.

151
00:10:18,276 --> 00:10:20,482
Let me tell it one more time.

152
00:10:20,655 --> 00:10:22,823
Don't play
that old record again.

153
00:10:22,995 --> 00:10:25,422
You get too emotional.

154
00:10:25,585 --> 00:10:27,378
Go on.

155
00:10:27,542 --> 00:10:30,543
So this is what happened,
Rafi miyan:

156
00:10:30,716 --> 00:10:34,676
I woke up one morning
and really had to pee,

157
00:10:34,849 --> 00:10:36,728
but it was really hot.

158
00:10:36,892 --> 00:10:39,146
So I'm thinking,
"Why is it so bloody hot?"

159
00:10:39,318 --> 00:10:41,533
And I look up

160
00:10:41,697 --> 00:10:44,199
and see that the fan
has stopped,

161
00:10:44,362 --> 00:10:46,693
but Tiwari is swinging.
He had hanged himself.

162
00:10:46,866 --> 00:10:49,158
So Zakir peed right then
and there.

163
00:10:49,331 --> 00:10:51,584
[laughing, chattering]

164
00:10:54,672 --> 00:10:56,965
Rafi miyan, think about it:

165
00:10:57,137 --> 00:11:00,187
that man left without a word.

166
00:11:00,349 --> 00:11:03,265
He didn't even leave a note.

167
00:11:03,437 --> 00:11:05,145
Not even a note.

168
00:11:06,449 --> 00:11:08,741
Who would he write it to,
anyway?

169
00:11:11,581 --> 00:11:12,874
To this day,

170
00:11:13,038 --> 00:11:17,210
to this day,
I can hear that man swinging...

171
00:11:17,383 --> 00:11:20,144
from this fan. Even now.

172
00:11:20,298 --> 00:11:22,052
[shuffling cards]

173
00:11:22,225 --> 00:11:25,276
I swear in God's name he still
paces around this room at night!

174
00:11:25,438 --> 00:11:28,699
Enough Zakir bhai,
you're ruining the party.

175
00:11:28,862 --> 00:11:30,492
[laughter]

176
00:11:30,656 --> 00:11:33,245
Rafi miyan, you should stop
sulking like this.

177
00:11:33,407 --> 00:11:36,238
Stop worrying
about your grandma.

178
00:11:36,409 --> 00:11:37,743
My mother,

179
00:11:37,916 --> 00:11:40,169
she used to call
and bug me all the time.

180
00:11:40,332 --> 00:11:44,005
It got so bad, I could barely
drive my rickshaw anymore.

181
00:11:46,594 --> 00:11:48,052
The food is delicious,
Rampyaari.

182
00:11:48,225 --> 00:11:50,143
Thank you, didi.

183
00:11:50,316 --> 00:11:52,742
Son? Eat properly.

184
00:11:52,896 --> 00:11:55,274
You have to finish it all.

185
00:11:55,447 --> 00:11:57,326
He doesn't eat well, Saloni.

186
00:11:57,489 --> 00:11:58,909
It's not just the food, Papa.

187
00:11:59,082 --> 00:12:02,217
It's the same with his studies.

188
00:12:02,371 --> 00:12:04,405
If you don't study, what
will you be when you grow up?

189
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,083
An actor!

190
00:12:06,255 --> 00:12:07,339
[light laughter]

191
00:12:10,351 --> 00:12:14,609
You know, Miloni wanted to be an
actress when she was in school.

192
00:12:14,771 --> 00:12:16,056
Really?

193
00:12:16,229 --> 00:12:18,233
The teachers in school, my God!

194
00:12:18,406 --> 00:12:21,494
They gave her trophy
after trophy for drama.

195
00:12:21,657 --> 00:12:24,074
You won trophies?

196
00:12:24,247 --> 00:12:27,296
Finally I had to go and tell
them, stop giving her prizes!

197
00:12:27,459 --> 00:12:29,377
If she does drama all the time,

198
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:34,432
when will she have time
for her academics?

199
00:12:34,595 --> 00:12:36,225
- Rampyaari?
- Yes, madam?

200
00:12:36,388 --> 00:12:38,431
- Bring out the dessert!
- Okay, madam.

201
00:12:40,185 --> 00:12:42,315
- [train rattling]
- [fan creaking rhythmically]

202
00:12:48,577 --> 00:12:50,247
[snoring]

203
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:54,390
[floorboards creak]

204
00:12:55,847 --> 00:12:58,226
Tiwari's ghost,

205
00:12:58,389 --> 00:13:00,009
you don't scare me.

206
00:13:04,152 --> 00:13:06,530
[floorboards creaking quietly]

207
00:13:20,513 --> 00:13:23,938
[train rattling and squealing]

208
00:13:27,189 --> 00:13:29,059
[unzips bag]

209
00:13:34,535 --> 00:13:36,280
<i>Dear Dadi, assalamu alaikum.</i>

210
00:13:39,206 --> 00:13:40,873
[beeps, whirrs]

211
00:13:41,046 --> 00:13:43,099
<i>I heard you've stopped taking
your medicine.</i>

212
00:13:43,262 --> 00:13:45,478
<i>Let me get straight
to the point.</i>

213
00:13:46,599 --> 00:13:48,316
[printer whirring]

214
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:50,781
<i>The thing is, Dadi,</i>

215
00:13:50,935 --> 00:13:52,814
<i>I've met a girl here.</i>

216
00:13:55,193 --> 00:13:57,820
<i>When I met her,</i>

217
00:13:57,993 --> 00:14:00,045
<i>I felt you had picked her out
for me.</i>

218
00:14:03,497 --> 00:14:07,631
<i>Her eyes are full of questions
but also full of answers.</i>

219
00:14:07,804 --> 00:14:12,274
<i>Her smile... takes away
all the troubles.</i>

220
00:14:14,392 --> 00:14:16,896
<i>And her laugh... Remember
the first rains on our farm?</i>

221
00:14:18,401 --> 00:14:20,405
<i>Her name is beautiful, too.</i>

222
00:14:22,122 --> 00:14:23,915
[song playing faintly in Hindi]

223
00:14:30,169 --> 00:14:35,472
♪ Oh, Noorie, Noorie... ♪

224
00:14:37,688 --> 00:14:39,443
<i>Her name is...</i>

225
00:14:39,606 --> 00:14:40,766
<i>Noorie.</i>

226
00:14:43,029 --> 00:14:46,080
<i>I'm sending you her photograph.
I hope you'll approve.</i>

227
00:14:47,201 --> 00:14:49,954
<i>Your obedient child, Rafiullah.</i>

228
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,793
[footsteps jingling]

229
00:14:57,511 --> 00:14:58,969
Anything else, didi?

230
00:14:59,142 --> 00:15:00,982
- Good night, didi.
- Good night.

231
00:15:06,699 --> 00:15:09,960
[train horn blowing]

232
00:15:14,169 --> 00:15:15,474
TEACHER:
A person shall be eligible

233
00:15:15,627 --> 00:15:17,344
for appointment
as an auditor of a company

234
00:15:17,508 --> 00:15:20,596
only if he is
a chartered accountant.

235
00:15:20,758 --> 00:15:22,964
Two: where a firm,

236
00:15:23,137 --> 00:15:25,390
including a limited
liability partnership,

237
00:15:25,563 --> 00:15:28,152
is appointed as an auditor
of a company,

238
00:15:28,316 --> 00:15:30,818
only the partners
who are chartered accountants

239
00:15:30,991 --> 00:15:33,370
shall be authorized
to act and sign

240
00:15:33,532 --> 00:15:35,489
on behalf of the firm.

241
00:15:35,662 --> 00:15:37,282
Three:

242
00:15:37,455 --> 00:15:39,747
under subsection three...
[voice fades]

243
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,339
[bird squawking]

244
00:15:41,503 --> 00:15:43,966
[beeps, clicks]

245
00:15:44,139 --> 00:15:46,643
What's the matter, Rafi miyan?

246
00:15:46,806 --> 00:15:47,967
[chuckles]

247
00:15:48,139 --> 00:15:51,725
You're drinking
like a fish today.

248
00:15:54,114 --> 00:15:56,119
His grandmother
is taking her medicine again.

249
00:15:56,281 --> 00:15:58,199
- Really?
- Wow!

250
00:15:58,372 --> 00:16:00,751
Did you agree to the marriage?

251
00:16:00,913 --> 00:16:01,997
No way.

252
00:16:04,548 --> 00:16:07,051
I told my grandma,

253
00:16:07,215 --> 00:16:09,544
"Listen up, Dadi!"

254
00:16:09,717 --> 00:16:11,635
"Listen up, Dadi."

255
00:16:11,808 --> 00:16:12,892
"Listen up, Dadi"?

256
00:16:13,064 --> 00:16:14,570
I mean,
"Please understand, Dadi."

257
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:16,526
[laughing]

258
00:16:18,531 --> 00:16:19,912
I told her, directly.

259
00:16:23,949 --> 00:16:27,076
- What did you tell her?
- What did you tell her?

260
00:16:27,248 --> 00:16:29,329
That's the most important thing.

261
00:16:29,502 --> 00:16:30,749
I said...

262
00:16:32,092 --> 00:16:36,259
"Rafiullah is the name of the bird 
that doesn't come in the hand."

263
00:16:36,810 --> 00:16:38,191
"Doesn't come in the hand"?

264
00:16:38,355 --> 00:16:39,150
Correct.

265
00:16:39,313 --> 00:16:40,522
Well said!

266
00:16:43,945 --> 00:16:46,698
Rafi miyan, don't lie to us.

267
00:16:46,871 --> 00:16:49,422
What did you really tell her?

268
00:16:49,584 --> 00:16:51,052
[train horn blowing
in distance]

269
00:16:51,205 --> 00:16:52,375
Well?

270
00:16:56,297 --> 00:16:58,254
Zakir bhai...

271
00:17:02,023 --> 00:17:05,485
I told her, directly...

272
00:17:05,648 --> 00:17:09,408
"Until I've paid
every cent of our debt..."

273
00:17:11,873 --> 00:17:14,961
"...and we have our family house
back, I won't get married."

274
00:17:15,124 --> 00:17:16,495
I told her directly.

275
00:17:18,173 --> 00:17:20,264
Well said, Rafi, well said!

276
00:17:21,473 --> 00:17:24,945
Rafi miyan, understand this:

277
00:17:25,097 --> 00:17:28,148
even a racehorse

278
00:17:28,321 --> 00:17:32,367
gets old one day
and then he can't run anymore.

279
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:38,083
Settle down.

280
00:17:38,247 --> 00:17:39,493
Get married.

281
00:17:41,008 --> 00:17:42,265
Well said!

282
00:17:43,847 --> 00:17:45,104
Get married.

283
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:49,218
What do you say?

284
00:17:49,390 --> 00:17:52,267
Zakir bhai,
I'm not a softie like you.

285
00:17:54,866 --> 00:17:56,324
I'm tough like...

286
00:17:58,578 --> 00:18:00,209
...a kulfi. A kulfi!

287
00:18:02,788 --> 00:18:04,169
Well said!

288
00:18:08,677 --> 00:18:10,384
What's a softie?

289
00:18:10,557 --> 00:18:11,938
[birds squawking]

290
00:18:12,101 --> 00:18:13,904
This is Noorie?

291
00:18:14,066 --> 00:18:15,610
[camera beeping]

292
00:18:16,895 --> 00:18:18,526
- Huh?
- Haan.

293
00:18:18,699 --> 00:18:20,492
[ship horn blowing]

294
00:18:24,578 --> 00:18:27,119
You couldn't choose
a less pretty girl?

295
00:18:31,464 --> 00:18:34,552
Your face is black
like doomsday.

296
00:18:35,722 --> 00:18:38,349
And look at her!

297
00:18:38,522 --> 00:18:41,696
If I were Dadi,
I'd come to see her directly.

298
00:18:46,703 --> 00:18:49,417
When is Dadi arriving?

299
00:18:49,579 --> 00:18:51,062
She's taking
the Firozpur Janta Express.

300
00:18:51,086 --> 00:18:53,598
It can take two days, or three.

301
00:18:56,216 --> 00:18:58,547
Just tell Dadi the truth.

302
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,264
What?

303
00:19:00,436 --> 00:19:03,447
You don't know Dadi,
she'll chew my head off.

304
00:19:03,611 --> 00:19:06,286
So tell her Noorie had
to leave town for work.

305
00:19:06,449 --> 00:19:09,327
She'll be back in a month.
She'll meet you next time.

306
00:19:09,489 --> 00:19:11,619
Until then,
long live the Republic!

307
00:19:18,754 --> 00:19:21,967
When we were children,

308
00:19:22,139 --> 00:19:25,102
the headmaster threw me
and my sisters out of school.

309
00:19:25,266 --> 00:19:26,724
We couldn't pay the fees.

310
00:19:27,903 --> 00:19:30,530
Dadi...

311
00:19:30,694 --> 00:19:33,235
stood outside the school
for three days.

312
00:19:34,991 --> 00:19:37,656
Until they took us back.

313
00:19:40,715 --> 00:19:43,593
- So?
- So?

314
00:19:46,969 --> 00:19:48,637
She didn't sit, she stood.

315
00:19:48,810 --> 00:19:50,565
For three whole days.

316
00:20:00,329 --> 00:20:01,997
So what are you going to do?

317
00:20:05,047 --> 00:20:06,591
- TEACHER: Yes?
- STUDENTS: No.

318
00:20:06,754 --> 00:20:08,586
TEACHER:
No? Sure?

319
00:20:08,758 --> 00:20:10,389
- Why?
- Is that you?

320
00:20:10,552 --> 00:20:12,221
Because he has the shares
in the company

321
00:20:12,393 --> 00:20:13,665
- that he is auditing,
- So pretty.

322
00:20:13,687 --> 00:20:15,318
and that is
a conflict of interest.

323
00:20:15,481 --> 00:20:17,149
TEACHER:
Right. Everyone understand?

324
00:20:17,322 --> 00:20:19,154
- STUDENTS: Yes, sir.
- TEACHER: What is it?

325
00:20:19,318 --> 00:20:20,698
STUDENTS:
Conflict of interest.

326
00:20:20,862 --> 00:20:22,766
- Give it to Sneha.
- TEACHER: Conflict of interest.

327
00:20:22,789 --> 00:20:24,668
Uh, example two.

328
00:20:24,832 --> 00:20:28,217
We have Mr. P.

329
00:20:28,381 --> 00:20:31,391
Now, Mr. P is a practicing
chartered accountant.

330
00:20:31,555 --> 00:20:33,895
He has a cousin, Mr. Q.

331
00:20:34,057 --> 00:20:38,488
Mr. Q holds interests
in a company, ABC Limited,

332
00:20:38,642 --> 00:20:41,021
of 90,000 rupees.

333
00:20:41,193 --> 00:20:43,245
Hmm? 90,000 rupees, huh?

334
00:20:44,742 --> 00:20:47,666
Now, is Mr. P,

335
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:49,921
the practicing
chartered accountant,

336
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:53,891
eligible to audit company,
ABC Limited?

337
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:56,260
So... What is this?

338
00:20:56,422 --> 00:20:59,136
- Sir, nothing.
- What are you doing?

339
00:20:59,309 --> 00:21:01,188
- S-Sorry, sir.
- Please give it to me.

340
00:21:07,442 --> 00:21:09,025
Whose is this?

341
00:21:21,723 --> 00:21:23,142
Where was I?

342
00:21:23,304 --> 00:21:24,762
- STUDENTS: Mr. P.
- Mr. P.

343
00:21:35,916 --> 00:21:38,419
90,000 rupees, uh, investment.

344
00:21:38,582 --> 00:21:39,809
Is he allowed to be the auditor?

345
00:21:39,963 --> 00:21:41,382
[overlapping responses]

346
00:21:41,545 --> 00:21:43,167
TEACHER:
No. Why no?

347
00:21:43,339 --> 00:21:45,132
[bus rumbling]

348
00:21:55,317 --> 00:21:57,149
♪ ♪

349
00:22:00,083 --> 00:22:01,925
[horns honking]

350
00:22:19,696 --> 00:22:21,490
♪ ♪

351
00:22:26,246 --> 00:22:28,203
Sir, can I have
my photograph back?

352
00:22:28,375 --> 00:22:31,252
You're a topper, right?

353
00:22:31,425 --> 00:22:33,046
Yes, sir.

354
00:22:41,696 --> 00:22:44,248
How are the classes going?

355
00:22:44,410 --> 00:22:45,417
Good.

356
00:22:50,664 --> 00:22:52,246
There's no problem then?

357
00:22:52,418 --> 00:22:53,415
No.

358
00:22:56,265 --> 00:22:57,309
Good.

359
00:23:12,789 --> 00:23:14,918
[indistinct chatter]

360
00:23:20,010 --> 00:23:21,813
[bell ringing]

361
00:23:29,064 --> 00:23:30,857
[laughter, chatter]

362
00:23:42,547 --> 00:23:44,341
[printer whirring]

363
00:23:52,272 --> 00:23:53,855
Thank you, madam.

364
00:24:04,174 --> 00:24:07,885
[cameras clicking]

365
00:24:16,191 --> 00:24:18,243
Rafi miyan, when does
your grandmother arrive?

366
00:24:18,407 --> 00:24:19,787
In two days.

367
00:24:19,951 --> 00:24:21,222
Don't forget to bring her over
to visit us.

368
00:24:21,244 --> 00:24:22,875
We want to pay our respects!

369
00:24:23,039 --> 00:24:24,707
When does Dadi arrive?

370
00:24:24,871 --> 00:24:25,992
- Rafi miyan!
- Rafi miyan!

371
00:24:35,975 --> 00:24:38,527
♪ ♪

372
00:24:42,028 --> 00:24:44,329
DRIVER:
Manish Nagar.

373
00:24:44,493 --> 00:24:46,333
Manish Nagar.
Chalo. Manish Nagar.

374
00:24:57,055 --> 00:24:58,350
[brakes squeal]

375
00:24:58,513 --> 00:24:59,847
[door opens]

376
00:25:05,063 --> 00:25:06,311
[door closes]

377
00:25:08,075 --> 00:25:09,868
[fan creaking rhythmically]

378
00:25:35,666 --> 00:25:37,546
[horns honking]

379
00:25:39,081 --> 00:25:40,539
[bell dinging]

380
00:25:44,509 --> 00:25:46,053
[brakes squeal]

381
00:25:46,226 --> 00:25:48,019
[door opens]

382
00:25:59,787 --> 00:26:01,915
[door closes]

383
00:26:03,249 --> 00:26:05,042
♪ ♪

384
00:26:19,533 --> 00:26:20,914
[brakes squeal]

385
00:26:21,077 --> 00:26:22,544
[door opens]

386
00:26:25,373 --> 00:26:27,004
[door closes]

387
00:26:36,556 --> 00:26:38,388
♪ ♪

388
00:26:57,808 --> 00:26:59,103
Here, madam.

389
00:27:00,475 --> 00:27:02,307
[birds squawking]

390
00:27:07,696 --> 00:27:09,279
Thank you.

391
00:27:33,321 --> 00:27:34,281
Wait!

392
00:27:44,341 --> 00:27:46,048
Why did you give me the photo?

393
00:27:48,599 --> 00:27:52,023
Madam, you asked for it, so...

394
00:27:52,186 --> 00:27:55,773
No. Why did you give it to me
in advance?

395
00:27:55,945 --> 00:27:59,446
You could've given it to me
once I'd met your grandmother.

396
00:28:02,754 --> 00:28:04,634
Why did you give it in advance?

397
00:28:05,546 --> 00:28:06,965
[clears throat quietly]

398
00:28:09,977 --> 00:28:11,357
Do you want it back?

399
00:28:11,521 --> 00:28:13,861
No, madam, you keep it.

400
00:28:14,023 --> 00:28:16,737
If you could meet her
just once...

401
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:18,320
But it's no problem.

402
00:28:31,295 --> 00:28:33,051
[lively chatter,
indistinct announcements]

403
00:28:33,224 --> 00:28:35,017
[horns honking]

404
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:51,962
Dadi. Dadi.

405
00:28:52,797 --> 00:28:54,466
Where were you?

406
00:28:54,629 --> 00:28:56,758
I'm on time.
Your train arrived early.

407
00:28:58,225 --> 00:28:59,606
How was the journey?

408
00:28:59,770 --> 00:29:03,317
A pregnant woman
was in my compartment.

409
00:29:04,814 --> 00:29:07,480
And she gave birth
to a daughter.

410
00:29:07,653 --> 00:29:09,360
Know what she named her?

411
00:29:09,532 --> 00:29:11,950
- What?
- Train Flower!

412
00:29:12,123 --> 00:29:13,877
- [cell phone ringing]
- Can you believe it?

413
00:29:14,041 --> 00:29:17,129
I stayed up all night
to throw a coin

414
00:29:17,301 --> 00:29:19,890
into the Gomti River,

415
00:29:20,053 --> 00:29:22,892
and someone else got
the grandchild!

416
00:29:23,055 --> 00:29:24,849
[phone continues ringing]

417
00:29:25,894 --> 00:29:27,639
Noorie didn't come?

418
00:29:27,812 --> 00:29:29,270
She had urgent work.

419
00:29:29,442 --> 00:29:31,486
What's more important than me?

420
00:29:31,658 --> 00:29:33,700
One second, Dadi...

421
00:29:33,863 --> 00:29:35,744
[Dadi continues speaking]

422
00:29:38,754 --> 00:29:40,423
Hello?

423
00:29:40,586 --> 00:29:42,457
Haan.

424
00:29:42,629 --> 00:29:44,298
[Rafi and Dadi
both continue speaking]

425
00:29:45,765 --> 00:29:47,942
- RAFI: Thank you.
- [Dadi speaking]

426
00:29:51,318 --> 00:29:52,450
Noorie says hello.

427
00:29:52,613 --> 00:29:55,029
Let it be.
"Hello-pello" nonsense.

428
00:29:55,193 --> 00:29:56,152
Let's go.

429
00:29:58,281 --> 00:30:00,074
♪ ♪

430
00:30:11,812 --> 00:30:13,779
[quiet chatter]

431
00:30:16,359 --> 00:30:18,161
[laughter]

432
00:30:21,614 --> 00:30:23,407
♪ ♪

433
00:30:26,121 --> 00:30:27,579
RAFI:
Madam?

434
00:30:37,937 --> 00:30:39,740
♪ ♪

435
00:30:48,707 --> 00:30:50,760
[horns honking]

436
00:31:02,191 --> 00:31:04,071
Dadi thinks your name is Noorie.

437
00:31:06,737 --> 00:31:09,202
The night I wrote the letter,

438
00:31:09,365 --> 00:31:11,618
a song was playing nearby.

439
00:31:11,791 --> 00:31:14,544
The song from that movie,
"Noorie."

440
00:31:18,927 --> 00:31:20,931
So I wrote
that your name is Noorie.

441
00:31:27,644 --> 00:31:29,811
I couldn't think
of anything else, so...

442
00:31:36,918 --> 00:31:38,798
And how did we meet?

443
00:31:40,332 --> 00:31:42,250
The same, at the Gateway.

444
00:31:48,849 --> 00:31:50,431
Is there anything else?

445
00:31:51,937 --> 00:31:53,356
I should know things.

446
00:31:54,526 --> 00:31:56,233
I have two elder sisters.

447
00:31:58,286 --> 00:32:01,086
And when we were kids,
our parents, they...

448
00:32:12,269 --> 00:32:14,072
I have an older sister, too.

449
00:32:19,615 --> 00:32:21,206
Sahib,

450
00:32:21,369 --> 00:32:23,834
are you and madam actors?

451
00:32:23,998 --> 00:32:25,341
From a drama company?

452
00:32:33,425 --> 00:32:35,304
Now it makes sense:

453
00:32:35,477 --> 00:32:38,489
a girl like her... with you.

454
00:32:38,641 --> 00:32:40,311
Give me back my change.

455
00:32:42,315 --> 00:32:44,147
[coins jingling]

456
00:32:46,036 --> 00:32:47,504
- Here.
- No, thanks.

457
00:32:50,208 --> 00:32:51,752
Have some.

458
00:32:51,915 --> 00:32:54,293
No, thanks, I'm full.

459
00:32:54,466 --> 00:32:55,636
You're full?

460
00:33:04,277 --> 00:33:08,123
Rafi says you're a student?

461
00:33:08,286 --> 00:33:10,665
I'm studying for my CA Inter
to be a...

462
00:33:10,827 --> 00:33:12,209
chartered accountant.

463
00:33:15,048 --> 00:33:20,476
If my Rafi had continued
his studies,

464
00:33:20,638 --> 00:33:24,485
he would've become a compounder
for sure.

465
00:33:24,647 --> 00:33:28,110
His uncle was a very well-known

466
00:33:28,272 --> 00:33:31,897
compounder in Kanpur.

467
00:33:32,070 --> 00:33:34,401
Big-time doctors

468
00:33:34,573 --> 00:33:37,162
would never make a move

469
00:33:37,335 --> 00:33:38,841
without his advice!

470
00:33:40,587 --> 00:33:42,668
Dadi, let it go.

471
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,672
Why should I let it go?

472
00:33:46,513 --> 00:33:49,726
I have a mother's heart.

473
00:33:49,899 --> 00:33:52,401
Soon, she'll be
a chartered boat,

474
00:33:52,565 --> 00:33:57,025
while you, as usual, will be
paddling with your anchor down.

475
00:33:57,197 --> 00:34:00,113
Look.
See what he's done to himself,

476
00:34:00,285 --> 00:34:02,788
working in the hot sun?

477
00:34:02,961 --> 00:34:04,591
He's become a black raisin.

478
00:34:04,754 --> 00:34:06,807
His skin used to be golden,

479
00:34:06,970 --> 00:34:08,514
just like wheat.

480
00:34:09,550 --> 00:34:11,256
Now look at him!

481
00:34:12,724 --> 00:34:14,478
Not what he used to be.

482
00:34:14,642 --> 00:34:16,022
Tell me,

483
00:34:16,186 --> 00:34:18,689
how are your parents?

484
00:34:21,826 --> 00:34:23,197
You didn't tell her?

485
00:34:27,589 --> 00:34:29,680
They're gone.

486
00:34:29,842 --> 00:34:31,176
Where?

487
00:34:31,339 --> 00:34:33,804
A wall in our mosque collapsed.

488
00:34:33,977 --> 00:34:36,144
And many people were crushed.

489
00:34:36,306 --> 00:34:37,918
My father tried
to save as many as he could

490
00:34:38,062 --> 00:34:39,894
before the other wall
fell on him.

491
00:34:42,780 --> 00:34:44,785
My mother was crushed to death,
too.

492
00:34:47,575 --> 00:34:49,033
And my older sister.

493
00:34:50,788 --> 00:34:53,205
So you're all alone
in this world?

494
00:34:55,219 --> 00:34:58,642
- Who do you live with?
- At the women's hostel.

495
00:35:07,571 --> 00:35:09,864
[spoon clinking in bowl]

496
00:35:12,501 --> 00:35:14,668
Is this something
to hide from me?

497
00:35:19,214 --> 00:35:23,223
I had meant to give you this
in a few days...

498
00:35:25,438 --> 00:35:28,776
...when we knew each other
better.

499
00:35:30,694 --> 00:35:33,906
But life is so unpredictable,
my child.

500
00:35:38,127 --> 00:35:39,967
I got this for you.

501
00:35:41,301 --> 00:35:43,468
They're very old.

502
00:35:43,631 --> 00:35:46,719
They don't make them
like these anymore.

503
00:35:48,935 --> 00:35:50,143
Here you go.

504
00:35:54,190 --> 00:35:55,696
I couldn't possibly.

505
00:35:55,860 --> 00:35:57,778
- What?
- They're yours.

506
00:35:57,949 --> 00:36:01,239
Now they're yours, I said.

507
00:36:02,955 --> 00:36:05,334
What are you looking at him for?

508
00:36:05,507 --> 00:36:07,472
- Keep them.
- Dadi.

509
00:36:07,636 --> 00:36:09,516
I need to go pee.

510
00:36:09,678 --> 00:36:10,638
Go.

511
00:36:17,188 --> 00:36:18,358
They're beautiful.

512
00:36:18,531 --> 00:36:20,746
[jewelry jingling]

513
00:36:23,373 --> 00:36:24,880
What will you tell her?

514
00:36:28,131 --> 00:36:29,675
I'll handle it.

515
00:36:33,760 --> 00:36:36,350
She wants to buy
a shalwar kameez tomorrow.

516
00:36:36,523 --> 00:36:37,980
She wants me to come along.

517
00:36:38,143 --> 00:36:39,975
[Rafi chuckles]

518
00:36:48,166 --> 00:36:50,294
Thanks for meeting Dadi, madam.

519
00:36:59,137 --> 00:37:01,055
Can you take more photos of me?

520
00:37:02,225 --> 00:37:03,730
Of course.

521
00:37:06,780 --> 00:37:08,871
Should we meet
at the same time tomorrow?

522
00:37:12,122 --> 00:37:13,964
♪ ♪

523
00:37:16,169 --> 00:37:17,914
[engine starts]

524
00:37:18,087 --> 00:37:19,670
Thank you, madam.

525
00:37:22,768 --> 00:37:24,772
I didn't think
she was nice at first:

526
00:37:24,935 --> 00:37:27,390
"I won't eat this,
I won't eat that..."

527
00:37:27,562 --> 00:37:29,183
I mean, she was behaving...

528
00:37:29,356 --> 00:37:31,312
like a fairy princess.

529
00:37:32,953 --> 00:37:34,621
But then I thought,

530
00:37:34,785 --> 00:37:40,001
"Maybe she can give me some
beautiful great-grandchildren

531
00:37:40,174 --> 00:37:42,466
that I can show off
in the village."

532
00:37:44,259 --> 00:37:46,005
Not that my Rafi
isn't a catch...

533
00:37:46,177 --> 00:37:49,093
[chuckling]

534
00:37:49,265 --> 00:37:53,063
He does have his grandfather's
crooked smile.

535
00:37:53,236 --> 00:37:55,413
Show them the smile. Show it!

536
00:37:55,577 --> 00:37:57,121
Smile for us, Rafi bhai.

537
00:37:57,283 --> 00:37:58,501
Smile.

538
00:37:58,665 --> 00:38:01,589
Give us a smile, please!

539
00:38:01,753 --> 00:38:03,881
[Zakir continues speaking]

540
00:38:04,044 --> 00:38:06,250
[laughter]

541
00:38:10,135 --> 00:38:12,302
[footsteps jingling]

542
00:38:17,989 --> 00:38:19,581
[jingling]

543
00:38:34,638 --> 00:38:36,384
♪ ♪

544
00:38:36,556 --> 00:38:37,975
[quiet chatter]

545
00:38:38,148 --> 00:38:39,941
[footsteps jingling]

546
00:38:50,788 --> 00:38:52,620
[jingling]

547
00:39:03,227 --> 00:39:05,020
[jewelry jingling]

548
00:39:19,674 --> 00:39:21,631
[footsteps jingling]

549
00:39:22,724 --> 00:39:24,191
Anything else, didi?

550
00:39:26,148 --> 00:39:27,529
Rampyaari.

551
00:39:27,692 --> 00:39:29,159
Yes, didi?

552
00:39:29,323 --> 00:39:31,327
Where did you get the anklets?

553
00:39:31,490 --> 00:39:32,574
These?

554
00:39:33,782 --> 00:39:35,863
From my village.

555
00:39:36,036 --> 00:39:37,868
Used to be my mother's.

556
00:39:38,961 --> 00:39:41,138
They're very old.

557
00:39:41,301 --> 00:39:42,308
They're nice.

558
00:39:42,461 --> 00:39:43,717
Thank you, didi.

559
00:39:43,881 --> 00:39:45,002
Listen.

560
00:39:45,808 --> 00:39:46,892
Sit, please.

561
00:39:48,896 --> 00:39:50,527
- Do you need something?
- No.

562
00:39:59,158 --> 00:40:00,741
How are things in the village?

563
00:40:03,588 --> 00:40:04,970
Good, didi.

564
00:40:05,132 --> 00:40:06,217
I mean...

565
00:40:08,049 --> 00:40:09,842
...what do people do at home?

566
00:40:11,645 --> 00:40:14,024
It's just farmland, didi.

567
00:40:14,186 --> 00:40:15,979
They all farm.

568
00:40:17,322 --> 00:40:18,368
And?

569
00:40:21,370 --> 00:40:22,750
They...

570
00:40:22,914 --> 00:40:24,544
do housework.

571
00:40:28,716 --> 00:40:30,682
Graze cattle...

572
00:40:36,599 --> 00:40:38,268
And in the evening?

573
00:40:40,982 --> 00:40:43,696
They come back from the fields.

574
00:40:46,247 --> 00:40:48,922
The power goes off at night.
No lights.

575
00:40:49,086 --> 00:40:50,927
[chuckles]

576
00:40:57,555 --> 00:40:59,558
There's a lot of peace there,
didi.

577
00:41:01,390 --> 00:41:02,973
I'll visit someday.

578
00:41:03,145 --> 00:41:05,898
The village?

579
00:41:06,071 --> 00:41:07,911
[laughs]

580
00:41:09,322 --> 00:41:10,740
What would you do there?

581
00:41:13,915 --> 00:41:15,958
Just look and see.

582
00:41:19,967 --> 00:41:21,636
Stay with us.

583
00:41:23,726 --> 00:41:25,730
I'll arrange everything for you.

584
00:41:27,352 --> 00:41:29,394
It would be an honor for me.

585
00:41:31,073 --> 00:41:32,329
Anything else, didi?

586
00:41:32,492 --> 00:41:34,918
- No.
- Biscuit?

587
00:41:35,081 --> 00:41:36,213
No.

588
00:41:36,376 --> 00:41:38,006
Rafi bhai!

589
00:41:38,169 --> 00:41:39,464
[snoring]

590
00:41:39,627 --> 00:41:40,922
Rafi bhai.

591
00:41:42,342 --> 00:41:45,017
- [snoring continues]
- Rafi bhai.

592
00:41:45,180 --> 00:41:48,144
Did they actually meet
or did you drug your grandma?

593
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:52,604
Rafi bhai!

594
00:41:54,070 --> 00:41:55,998
Rafi bhai.

595
00:41:57,993 --> 00:42:02,423
Rafi got both his sisters
married off.

596
00:42:03,584 --> 00:42:05,205
Single-handedly!

597
00:42:06,422 --> 00:42:08,044
And he said to me,

598
00:42:08,217 --> 00:42:09,885
"Dadi!

599
00:42:10,057 --> 00:42:12,771
"Don't worry about a thing!

600
00:42:12,935 --> 00:42:16,311
God willing,
everything will be okay."

601
00:42:16,484 --> 00:42:18,910
Forget about it, Dadi,
it's old news.

602
00:42:20,281 --> 00:42:24,079
"Old news," he says.

603
00:42:24,241 --> 00:42:26,918
Maybe it's old news to you!

604
00:42:27,963 --> 00:42:29,804
I'll say what I want.

605
00:42:32,097 --> 00:42:34,475
Rafi paid for banquets

606
00:42:34,638 --> 00:42:37,093
for both of his sisters.

607
00:42:37,266 --> 00:42:40,440
The samosas were so good.

608
00:42:40,613 --> 00:42:42,578
People were eating them

609
00:42:42,732 --> 00:42:46,156
and stuffing their pockets
with them to take them home!

610
00:42:46,328 --> 00:42:48,247
When he saw them doing it,

611
00:42:48,409 --> 00:42:51,411
he turned to me and said,

612
00:42:51,584 --> 00:42:53,041
"Dadi!

613
00:42:53,214 --> 00:42:55,928
Don't stop anyone today!"

614
00:42:56,092 --> 00:42:58,096
[Dadi laughing]

615
00:43:01,185 --> 00:43:02,766
Tell me,

616
00:43:02,939 --> 00:43:06,238
what color do you like best?

617
00:43:07,696 --> 00:43:08,780
Well?

618
00:43:11,868 --> 00:43:14,246
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

619
00:43:14,419 --> 00:43:16,720
Why not?

620
00:43:16,884 --> 00:43:18,514
How's that possible?!

621
00:43:19,512 --> 00:43:21,554
Listen, Rafi.

622
00:43:21,718 --> 00:43:23,299
Give me that one.

623
00:43:23,472 --> 00:43:25,476
The orange one.

624
00:43:27,271 --> 00:43:30,396
Look at this color.
It'll look so nice on you.

625
00:43:31,278 --> 00:43:32,612
What do you say?

626
00:43:32,785 --> 00:43:35,997
Let's put it on you.
There you go.

627
00:43:36,161 --> 00:43:39,200
Look how it brightens you up!

628
00:43:39,373 --> 00:43:41,589
[clanking, whirring]

629
00:43:44,677 --> 00:43:46,260
[baby crying]

630
00:43:46,432 --> 00:43:48,686
[elevator stops]

631
00:43:54,527 --> 00:43:56,022
[doorbell rings]

632
00:43:57,115 --> 00:43:59,868
[chatter, light laughter]

633
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:01,795
Here's Miloni!

634
00:44:04,749 --> 00:44:06,840
India's number one herself!

635
00:44:07,013 --> 00:44:08,394
Join us, please.

636
00:44:10,973 --> 00:44:12,144
Please sit.

637
00:44:13,352 --> 00:44:15,644
How are you, child?

638
00:44:15,817 --> 00:44:18,531
I am Hasmukh, your father's
business associate.

639
00:44:18,694 --> 00:44:20,362
Not "business associate."

640
00:44:20,535 --> 00:44:21,705
You're like family!

641
00:44:21,869 --> 00:44:24,333
[laughter]

642
00:44:26,251 --> 00:44:28,054
♪ ♪

643
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:32,887
[chatter resumes]

644
00:44:38,853 --> 00:44:40,560
- Cola, didi?
- Nahin.

645
00:44:41,654 --> 00:44:42,910
WOMAN:
Thank you.

646
00:44:43,073 --> 00:44:46,746
His son is going to the USA
to do his MBA!

647
00:44:46,909 --> 00:44:48,827
HASMUKH:
Here.

648
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:50,965
This is his photo, Chintan.

649
00:44:52,213 --> 00:44:53,469
[chatter continues]

650
00:44:53,632 --> 00:44:54,590
Mm. Handsome.

651
00:44:54,629 --> 00:44:55,799
Want to see?

652
00:44:57,429 --> 00:45:00,067
Do you have a photo of Miloni?

653
00:45:00,230 --> 00:45:02,234
A recent photo?

654
00:45:02,397 --> 00:45:03,567
There should be one somewhere.

655
00:45:03,731 --> 00:45:06,943
Can we send it to you?

656
00:45:07,115 --> 00:45:10,664
Who needs a photo when
you've seen her face-to-face?

657
00:45:10,828 --> 00:45:12,458
You're right.

658
00:45:12,621 --> 00:45:15,162
KANTI:
Personal touch is always better.

659
00:45:15,335 --> 00:45:17,004
HASMUKH [chuckling]:
Right.

660
00:45:19,171 --> 00:45:20,417
I have a photo.

661
00:45:20,590 --> 00:45:22,134
What photo?

662
00:45:22,307 --> 00:45:25,070
I had it taken at the Gateway
of India the other day.

663
00:45:26,604 --> 00:45:28,982
Would you like it?

664
00:45:29,155 --> 00:45:30,487
It's a nice photo.

665
00:45:31,735 --> 00:45:32,693
One moment.

666
00:45:35,743 --> 00:45:37,326
DADI: <i>
Rafi?</i>

667
00:45:37,498 --> 00:45:40,202
I was thinking
you should start a business.

668
00:45:42,303 --> 00:45:45,477
Your work isn't steady.

669
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:47,645
It doesn't make you
enough money,

670
00:45:47,808 --> 00:45:50,436
all this running around
for a few rupees.

671
00:45:50,609 --> 00:45:52,277
Don't worry, I'll do it.

672
00:45:52,441 --> 00:45:55,442
Start a small factory.

673
00:45:55,615 --> 00:45:57,791
You need a proper business.

674
00:45:57,955 --> 00:45:59,211
Okay, Dadi.

675
00:45:59,374 --> 00:46:01,216
I will.

676
00:46:01,368 --> 00:46:06,797
If the girl makes more money
than you,

677
00:46:06,970 --> 00:46:10,145
who will you show your face
to then?

678
00:46:10,307 --> 00:46:14,565
And what will your kids say?
Ever consider that?

679
00:46:14,728 --> 00:46:18,315
Dad eats what Mom earns?

680
00:46:20,828 --> 00:46:24,750
Son, I even worry
about your kids.

681
00:46:24,913 --> 00:46:28,040
Stop it, Dadi.
God is watching over everyone.

682
00:46:28,213 --> 00:46:31,847
You've finally found a girl,

683
00:46:32,010 --> 00:46:35,357
and if you don't make
more money,

684
00:46:35,520 --> 00:46:38,110
you'll lose her.

685
00:46:41,610 --> 00:46:44,784
Don't worry,
I'll start a factory. Okay?

686
00:46:44,948 --> 00:46:50,366
I've seen the world.
A mother's heart can only weep.

687
00:46:50,539 --> 00:46:53,540
Should I place a stone over it?

688
00:46:53,713 --> 00:46:56,505
Don't.
Don't place a stone over it.

689
00:46:56,677 --> 00:46:58,422
Why would I place a stone
over it?

690
00:46:58,594 --> 00:47:00,763
That's what I'm saying:
don't do it.

691
00:47:02,229 --> 00:47:04,406
It's obvious...

692
00:47:04,570 --> 00:47:06,573
Why would I place a stone
over it?

693
00:47:08,703 --> 00:47:11,542
You remember what happened
with Kunjiben, right?

694
00:47:13,411 --> 00:47:15,666
Once she qualifies,

695
00:47:15,839 --> 00:47:18,763
she'll find a good job
and a good husband as well.

696
00:47:18,927 --> 00:47:21,304
Don't be so naive.

697
00:47:21,468 --> 00:47:23,932
A good match
doesn't come by every day.

698
00:47:27,980 --> 00:47:29,937
His son is going to the USA.

699
00:47:30,109 --> 00:47:33,821
And maybe Miloni
could also study there.

700
00:47:33,993 --> 00:47:36,631
We can't send her there
ourselves, can we?

701
00:47:37,330 --> 00:47:39,123
♪ ♪

702
00:47:51,860 --> 00:47:53,653
[ship horn blowing]

703
00:47:54,526 --> 00:47:56,482
Look, look.

704
00:47:56,655 --> 00:47:58,909
It's a miracle of God.

705
00:47:59,081 --> 00:48:03,176
My Rafi has the same crooked
smile as his grandfather.

706
00:48:03,340 --> 00:48:04,548
[Dadi laughing]

707
00:48:04,711 --> 00:48:06,840
How did you meet
Rafi's grandfather?

708
00:48:07,013 --> 00:48:09,890
Oh, forget it.
That's ancient history.

709
00:48:11,012 --> 00:48:13,976
How did you two meet?

710
00:48:15,903 --> 00:48:18,953
We met at the Gateway of India.
I told you, remember?

711
00:48:19,116 --> 00:48:20,074
And then?

712
00:48:20,152 --> 00:48:21,657
Then...

713
00:48:24,334 --> 00:48:25,964
I went for a stroll.

714
00:48:27,708 --> 00:48:29,503
And...

715
00:48:29,675 --> 00:48:31,976
I heard this voice calling me
from behind.

716
00:48:32,140 --> 00:48:35,189
I turned around and there he was
with that crooked smile.

717
00:48:35,352 --> 00:48:38,105
[Dadi laughing]

718
00:48:38,268 --> 00:48:40,224
Then he took my photograph

719
00:48:40,397 --> 00:48:41,816
and wouldn't accept any money
from me.

720
00:48:41,941 --> 00:48:44,195
Wouldn't accept any money?

721
00:48:44,367 --> 00:48:45,749
I mean...

722
00:48:45,911 --> 00:48:47,503
What do you mean?

723
00:48:49,661 --> 00:48:51,119
Tell me more.

724
00:48:53,670 --> 00:48:57,007
When I saw the photograph...

725
00:48:57,180 --> 00:48:58,772
I didn't see myself.

726
00:48:58,936 --> 00:49:00,019
Why not?

727
00:49:03,942 --> 00:49:06,454
I saw someone else.

728
00:49:06,607 --> 00:49:08,276
She was happier than me.

729
00:49:09,446 --> 00:49:10,492
DADI:
Mm.

730
00:49:10,665 --> 00:49:12,045
And prettier than me.

731
00:49:13,206 --> 00:49:15,076
[Dadi chuckling]

732
00:49:20,427 --> 00:49:22,393
And then we started meeting
every day.

733
00:49:26,776 --> 00:49:30,162
Now, listen to my story.

734
00:49:31,235 --> 00:49:33,192
In the old days,

735
00:49:33,365 --> 00:49:38,333
you had to get married when
your parents said so, but...

736
00:49:38,495 --> 00:49:40,711
[horn honking]

737
00:49:58,329 --> 00:49:59,710
[horn honks]

738
00:50:18,449 --> 00:50:20,329
[thunder rumbling softly]

739
00:50:27,838 --> 00:50:29,680
Is there a place for chai?

740
00:50:30,926 --> 00:50:33,478
I know a place nearby.

741
00:50:33,640 --> 00:50:35,606
Let's go have chai.

742
00:50:43,778 --> 00:50:45,236
Chai is good.

743
00:50:46,539 --> 00:50:47,672
Very good.

744
00:50:51,622 --> 00:50:53,626
I've noticed,
you don't drink cola.

745
00:50:55,219 --> 00:50:58,182
You always refuse cola.
You don't like it?

746
00:51:03,735 --> 00:51:05,491
Remember Campa Cola?

747
00:51:05,654 --> 00:51:07,072
Haan.

748
00:51:09,365 --> 00:51:11,494
When I was a child,

749
00:51:11,667 --> 00:51:14,083
my grandfather used to buy me
Campa Cola every day.

750
00:51:17,967 --> 00:51:21,429
Then he died and they stopped
making Campa Cola.

751
00:51:21,593 --> 00:51:22,839
RAFI:
Mm.

752
00:51:23,012 --> 00:51:25,928
I don't feel like drinking
any other cola.

753
00:51:28,689 --> 00:51:32,401
I understand.
Nothing wrong with that!

754
00:51:32,574 --> 00:51:37,963
My father used to take us for
kulfi at the end of each month.

755
00:51:38,126 --> 00:51:39,719
Now if I ever eat kulfi,

756
00:51:39,881 --> 00:51:42,470
it has to be on the last day
of the month.

757
00:51:42,634 --> 00:51:44,265
Otherwise, I don't.

758
00:51:55,782 --> 00:51:57,250
- Let me get it.
- No, no.

759
00:51:57,413 --> 00:51:59,043
You can get it tomorrow.

760
00:51:59,206 --> 00:52:00,663
Tomorrow...

761
00:52:00,827 --> 00:52:03,118
Dadi is going to Nalasopara.

762
00:52:03,291 --> 00:52:07,214
My cousin Zohra lives there.

763
00:52:07,386 --> 00:52:09,554
So, tomorrow...

764
00:52:09,718 --> 00:52:11,673
we won't be able to meet.

765
00:52:11,846 --> 00:52:13,217
Haan.

766
00:52:20,027 --> 00:52:23,489
But if you happen to have time,
we could go to a movie tomorrow.

767
00:52:27,373 --> 00:52:30,960
Where do you go for movies?
I mean, in what movie theater?

768
00:52:31,133 --> 00:52:35,132
Usually, I don't have the time.

769
00:52:35,304 --> 00:52:38,641
The problem is that
there's no time these days.

770
00:52:38,814 --> 00:52:41,328
It feels like everyone's always
running, running, running,

771
00:52:41,480 --> 00:52:42,814
these days.

772
00:52:59,261 --> 00:53:01,477
[song playing in Hindi
over car radio]

773
00:53:11,699 --> 00:53:15,287
Sir, can you turn the volume up,
please?

774
00:53:15,459 --> 00:53:17,252
[music volume increases]

775
00:53:30,402 --> 00:53:32,281
[song continues over speakers,
projector rattling]

776
00:54:01,042 --> 00:54:02,884
♪ ♪

777
00:54:05,962 --> 00:54:07,718
- [rat squeaking, scurrying]
- [gasps]

778
00:54:14,604 --> 00:54:16,522
Just a rat scuttling
over your feet.

779
00:54:16,694 --> 00:54:18,411
It's gone now.

780
00:54:18,574 --> 00:54:19,955
Don't worry.

781
00:54:27,378 --> 00:54:29,344
[song fades]

782
00:54:31,674 --> 00:54:33,381
[footsteps jingling]

783
00:54:33,554 --> 00:54:35,645
Anything else, didi?

784
00:54:35,808 --> 00:54:37,055
No.

785
00:54:38,311 --> 00:54:39,807
Biscuit?

786
00:54:43,241 --> 00:54:45,706
[beeping, clicking]

787
00:54:45,868 --> 00:54:47,921
<i>[printer whirring]</i>

788
00:54:50,961 --> 00:54:53,464
- [beeping, clicking] <i>
- [printer whirring]</i>

789
00:54:59,640 --> 00:55:01,932
Dadi was right.

790
00:55:02,105 --> 00:55:03,447
She looks nice
in the photograph

791
00:55:03,610 --> 00:55:04,781
but just so-so in real life.

792
00:55:04,944 --> 00:55:05,902
Shut up.

793
00:55:05,941 --> 00:55:07,312
Why are you angry?

794
00:55:07,485 --> 00:55:08,694
Who's angry?

795
00:55:10,573 --> 00:55:12,117
[speaking Hindi]

796
00:55:13,709 --> 00:55:15,503
30 rupees, 30 rupees.

797
00:55:17,257 --> 00:55:18,591
[Rafi speaking Hindi]

798
00:55:19,761 --> 00:55:21,602
Sir, 30 rupees.

799
00:55:21,766 --> 00:55:23,185
Sir, sir.

800
00:55:24,229 --> 00:55:25,773
What are they doing?

801
00:55:28,612 --> 00:55:30,991
Looks like they're buying
ice candy.

802
00:55:42,969 --> 00:55:45,395
It's been years
since I've had one of these.

803
00:55:45,549 --> 00:55:46,844
You have one, too.

804
00:55:47,017 --> 00:55:49,145
- You shouldn't have it.
- Why not?

805
00:55:49,309 --> 00:55:51,438
It's exam time.
You'll fall sick.

806
00:55:51,610 --> 00:55:53,989
Why would she get sick?

807
00:55:54,152 --> 00:55:57,240
Trying to save money
all the time!

808
00:55:57,412 --> 00:56:00,539
Be quiet and buy us both
one ice candy each!

809
00:56:07,885 --> 00:56:09,429
Rafi bhai?

810
00:56:09,592 --> 00:56:12,556
Buy an ice candy for me, too.

811
00:56:15,394 --> 00:56:16,603
Give me one!

812
00:56:18,905 --> 00:56:20,536
[Dadi speaks Hindi]

813
00:56:20,698 --> 00:56:22,444
Mmm...

814
00:56:22,616 --> 00:56:24,409
<i>[Dadi laughing]</i>

815
00:56:25,953 --> 00:56:28,879
Dadi forced you
to eat ice candy.

816
00:56:29,042 --> 00:56:31,085
No problem.

817
00:56:32,265 --> 00:56:33,472
She's always been like that.

818
00:56:33,636 --> 00:56:35,008
She's very nice.

819
00:56:42,401 --> 00:56:45,029
When we were little,

820
00:56:45,201 --> 00:56:46,832
at dinnertime,

821
00:56:46,996 --> 00:56:50,927
Dadi would make us laugh
so hard.

822
00:56:53,421 --> 00:56:55,962
We would forget we hadn't eaten.

823
00:56:58,551 --> 00:56:59,971
We forgot that we were hungry.

824
00:57:00,144 --> 00:57:02,733
And that there was no food
at home.

825
00:57:02,897 --> 00:57:05,025
[passing car honks horn]

826
00:57:06,109 --> 00:57:07,940
♪ ♪

827
00:57:10,664 --> 00:57:13,091
There's something...

828
00:57:13,244 --> 00:57:14,999
purple on your lips.

829
00:57:15,171 --> 00:57:16,466
[car honks horn]

830
00:57:17,377 --> 00:57:18,337
Here.

831
00:57:20,428 --> 00:57:21,722
A bit higher.

832
00:57:24,849 --> 00:57:27,601
[horn honking]

833
00:57:27,774 --> 00:57:31,284
So, young lady,
when did this problem begin?

834
00:57:31,446 --> 00:57:33,749
- Last night.
- Last night?

835
00:57:33,911 --> 00:57:36,463
She had ice candy
from the street, Doctor.

836
00:57:36,625 --> 00:57:37,585
[laughing]

837
00:57:37,661 --> 00:57:41,085
Most adventurous young lady!

838
00:57:41,257 --> 00:57:44,144
I remember your grandfather.

839
00:57:44,298 --> 00:57:47,933
He used to bring you in
when you were this little.

840
00:57:48,096 --> 00:57:53,188
You used to love that cola.
Which one was it?

841
00:57:53,361 --> 00:57:57,370
- Campa Cola.
- Campa Cola, that's it!

842
00:57:57,532 --> 00:58:01,369
Don't worry at all. It's
a very simple case of gastro.

843
00:58:01,541 --> 00:58:03,211
Doctor.

844
00:58:03,373 --> 00:58:05,713
She should know better than
eating things on the street.

845
00:58:05,886 --> 00:58:07,469
[doctor chuckling]

846
00:58:07,631 --> 00:58:10,719
The longer I live,
the more pain I have.

847
00:58:10,892 --> 00:58:13,069
But the longer I live,

848
00:58:13,223 --> 00:58:15,390
the pain hurts less.

849
00:58:15,563 --> 00:58:18,814
If your daughter eats
street food every day,

850
00:58:18,986 --> 00:58:23,244
she'll become immune to it.

851
00:58:23,407 --> 00:58:25,325
She has her CA Inter exams
coming up.

852
00:58:25,498 --> 00:58:26,495
CA Inter exam?

853
00:58:26,668 --> 00:58:28,337
Young lady?

854
00:58:28,500 --> 00:58:30,331
No street food it is!

855
00:58:30,504 --> 00:58:33,545
Mr. Shah?
Here's the prescription.

856
00:58:33,717 --> 00:58:37,889
You can pick it up outside...

857
00:58:38,062 --> 00:58:39,682
Rafi?

858
00:58:39,855 --> 00:58:41,773
- Hey, Rafi!
- Hmm?

859
00:58:41,946 --> 00:58:44,411
Wake up! Stop this hmmm, hmmm!

860
00:58:44,573 --> 00:58:46,290
I don't understand.

861
00:58:46,454 --> 00:58:48,208
Why didn't she come today?

862
00:58:48,371 --> 00:58:50,663
I hope she's okay.

863
00:58:50,836 --> 00:58:54,010
I told you not
to make her eat ice candy.

864
00:58:54,174 --> 00:58:57,012
She must've fallen ill
because of you. What else?

865
00:58:57,176 --> 00:59:00,014
How could she fall ill?

866
00:59:00,186 --> 00:59:03,735
I mean,
we all ate the same thing.

867
00:59:03,899 --> 00:59:05,270
Go to sleep, Dadi.

868
00:59:05,443 --> 00:59:08,943
How can I sleep, son?

869
00:59:09,115 --> 00:59:11,743
Where did you find such
a delicate girl

870
00:59:11,916 --> 00:59:14,716
who eats just one ice candy
and falls sick?

871
00:59:17,210 --> 00:59:18,965
Don't worry, Dadi jaan.

872
00:59:20,595 --> 00:59:23,357
My Ruksana
was also very delicate.

873
00:59:23,520 --> 00:59:26,694
Her family pampered her a lot.

874
00:59:26,858 --> 00:59:29,658
After we got married, she
adjusted to our circumstances.

875
00:59:31,902 --> 00:59:35,662
Her parents must've given her
a comfortable life.

876
00:59:35,824 --> 00:59:39,708
Rafi's love will help her
digest ice candy someday.

877
00:59:39,881 --> 00:59:43,219
Don't worry. Go to sleep.

878
00:59:43,382 --> 00:59:44,418
Sleep now.

879
00:59:46,096 --> 00:59:48,801
[Dadi groaning quietly]

880
00:59:53,528 --> 00:59:56,156
[creaking]

881
00:59:56,320 --> 00:59:58,611
What's that sound?

882
00:59:58,784 --> 01:00:01,038
Tiwari has just joined us.

883
01:00:01,211 --> 01:00:02,544
Who's Tiwari?

884
01:00:02,706 --> 01:00:04,912
Tiwari is our resident ghost.

885
01:00:05,085 --> 01:00:07,626
We've all heard his steps, Dadi.

886
01:00:07,799 --> 01:00:10,552
No one gets peace in Mumbai,
not even in death.

887
01:00:15,856 --> 01:00:17,936
Easy, easy. Careful.

888
01:00:20,286 --> 01:00:22,127
[chatter continues]

889
01:00:29,300 --> 01:00:30,931
Good-bye, friends.

890
01:00:32,265 --> 01:00:33,846
Parting is hard.

891
01:00:36,724 --> 01:00:38,478
I'll miss you a lot.

892
01:00:41,155 --> 01:00:43,159
[music playing,
audience cheering over TV]

893
01:00:43,322 --> 01:00:45,326
[quiet chatter]

894
01:00:50,207 --> 01:00:52,164
Don't trouble yourself, Dadi.

895
01:00:52,337 --> 01:00:54,591
It's no trouble at all,
my child.

896
01:00:57,717 --> 01:01:00,220
I told him
to bring Noorie along,

897
01:01:00,393 --> 01:01:02,944
but she's studying
for her exams.

898
01:01:04,478 --> 01:01:06,061
Poor girl.

899
01:01:06,233 --> 01:01:08,439
She's all alone in the hostel.

900
01:01:08,612 --> 01:01:10,779
Had she come,

901
01:01:10,952 --> 01:01:15,373
she would've loved your biryani.

902
01:01:15,545 --> 01:01:19,180
It's very good.
Very tasty, really.

903
01:01:41,968 --> 01:01:43,761
[engine starts]

904
01:01:57,370 --> 01:01:59,997
[horns honking]

905
01:02:00,160 --> 01:02:01,743
Evening outing, sir?

906
01:02:03,708 --> 01:02:05,080
Very good.

907
01:02:07,296 --> 01:02:09,463
Are you from up north, sir?

908
01:02:12,350 --> 01:02:13,846
- Haan.
- Ah.

909
01:02:14,019 --> 01:02:16,225
I knew it the moment you spoke!

910
01:02:16,397 --> 01:02:18,727
I'm from Gonda, and you?

911
01:02:18,900 --> 01:02:19,983
Balia.

912
01:02:20,156 --> 01:02:21,663
Balia!

913
01:02:21,825 --> 01:02:23,781
What are the odds?

914
01:02:23,954 --> 01:02:26,467
Your home is only 40 kilometers
from mine!

915
01:02:26,630 --> 01:02:29,804
I can leave my house at dawn and
be at your house by breakfast!

916
01:02:33,055 --> 01:02:34,772
Have you been to his village,
madam?

917
01:02:36,805 --> 01:02:39,184
No?! You should definitely go.

918
01:02:39,357 --> 01:02:40,488
You'll love it.

919
01:02:43,740 --> 01:02:45,082
You know, madam?

920
01:02:45,245 --> 01:02:47,288
A friend of mine, my roommate,

921
01:02:47,451 --> 01:02:50,117
his wife was also from Mumbai...

922
01:02:50,290 --> 01:02:52,371
Brother,
please focus on your driving.

923
01:02:52,543 --> 01:02:54,375
This is my daily work.

924
01:02:54,548 --> 01:02:57,425
This is what I do every day:
talk and drive.

925
01:02:58,767 --> 01:03:02,067
One eye on the road, always.

926
01:03:02,229 --> 01:03:03,697
So where were we, madam?

927
01:03:03,860 --> 01:03:07,159
Getting back to my friend
and his wife...

928
01:03:07,322 --> 01:03:10,285
Why should we care
about your friend?

929
01:03:10,449 --> 01:03:12,491
Be quiet and focus on driving,
please.

930
01:03:20,260 --> 01:03:21,381
You know what?

931
01:03:21,554 --> 01:03:23,683
This is too much!

932
01:03:23,846 --> 01:03:25,573
One moment, I'm your brother
from the village.

933
01:03:25,727 --> 01:03:28,852
The next, I'm a stranger.

934
01:03:29,025 --> 01:03:30,521
You told me to shut my mouth!

935
01:03:30,694 --> 01:03:32,362
I didn't tell you
to shut your mouth.

936
01:03:32,535 --> 01:03:34,913
I just told you to...

937
01:03:35,077 --> 01:03:38,242
drive safely.
That's all I said.

938
01:03:38,414 --> 01:03:40,581
Sir, I'm an educated man.

939
01:03:40,754 --> 01:03:42,384
When did I say you weren't?

940
01:03:42,547 --> 01:03:44,198
I have an M.A.
from Banaras Hindu University

941
01:03:44,264 --> 01:03:45,770
in English Literature.

942
01:03:50,604 --> 01:03:52,646
It's all God's will.

943
01:03:55,284 --> 01:03:59,167
♪ Some of us have
to drive a taxi ♪

944
01:03:59,331 --> 01:04:03,503
♪ While others get to paint
the town red. ♪

945
01:04:06,466 --> 01:04:07,722
[driver honks horn]

946
01:04:07,885 --> 01:04:09,228
Keep it moving!

947
01:04:09,391 --> 01:04:11,482
Get a bit closer.

948
01:04:13,352 --> 01:04:14,973
[camera clicks]

949
01:04:15,146 --> 01:04:18,109
And now:
put your arm around her.

950
01:04:21,370 --> 01:04:23,959
She's not a live wire!

951
01:04:25,666 --> 01:04:27,632
Now look at each other.

952
01:04:29,752 --> 01:04:32,044
Smile, please!

953
01:04:33,348 --> 01:04:34,431
[camera beeps, clicks]

954
01:04:35,852 --> 01:04:36,896
[camera clicks]

955
01:04:37,059 --> 01:04:39,265
- Show me.
- One second, Dadi.

956
01:04:39,438 --> 01:04:40,608
Show me!

957
01:04:40,772 --> 01:04:42,439
Just a second!

958
01:04:42,612 --> 01:04:43,408
Mm, mm.

959
01:04:43,572 --> 01:04:45,365
Look, what a nice photo!

960
01:04:45,538 --> 01:04:49,172
Yes, it's a very nice photo!

961
01:04:51,627 --> 01:04:53,756
Oh, wow, wow...

962
01:04:56,930 --> 01:04:59,645
Look, they look so nice
together.

963
01:05:01,975 --> 01:05:07,317
Looks like a rasgulla and a
gulab jamun on the same plate!

964
01:05:07,489 --> 01:05:09,082
[Dadi laughing]

965
01:05:09,245 --> 01:05:11,087
[footsteps jingling]

966
01:05:13,916 --> 01:05:16,246
[Dadi and Banke chattering]

967
01:05:16,418 --> 01:05:18,711
[footsteps jingling]

968
01:05:26,018 --> 01:05:27,899
[sets dishes on table]

969
01:05:48,058 --> 01:05:50,013
Miloni?

970
01:05:50,186 --> 01:05:54,896
Do you remember Hasmukh bhai
from the other day?

971
01:05:55,068 --> 01:05:57,235
His son Chintan is leaving soon
for the USA.

972
01:05:57,408 --> 01:06:00,324
We were thinking,
why don't you both...

973
01:06:00,496 --> 01:06:02,242
meet each other?

974
01:06:02,414 --> 01:06:04,207
Just as friends.

975
01:06:10,930 --> 01:06:12,974
Okay.

976
01:06:13,146 --> 01:06:15,322
Good.
[chuckles]

977
01:06:21,451 --> 01:06:23,254
♪ ♪

978
01:06:34,475 --> 01:06:35,855
Anything else?

979
01:06:50,664 --> 01:06:52,706
Need anything, didi?

980
01:07:08,444 --> 01:07:10,237
He's not my boyfriend.

981
01:07:15,042 --> 01:07:16,874
You're smart and educated, didi.

982
01:07:20,221 --> 01:07:22,225
I am a nobody.

983
01:07:27,606 --> 01:07:29,476
Don't worry.

984
01:07:29,649 --> 01:07:31,528
I won't tell madam or sir
a thing.

985
01:07:34,952 --> 01:07:36,535
Thank you.

986
01:07:42,260 --> 01:07:43,344
Didi?

987
01:07:55,408 --> 01:07:56,991
What about...

988
01:07:57,154 --> 01:07:59,619
the boy they're having you meet?

989
01:08:05,631 --> 01:08:08,346
Sir and madam were saying...

990
01:08:08,509 --> 01:08:10,177
What were they saying?

991
01:08:12,393 --> 01:08:15,318
This boy they want you
to meet...

992
01:08:17,860 --> 01:08:19,566
He used to be fat.

993
01:08:22,031 --> 01:08:23,450
Now he's thin.

994
01:08:25,455 --> 01:08:26,912
Meet him and see.

995
01:08:29,752 --> 01:08:31,670
What if he gets fat again?

996
01:08:34,969 --> 01:08:36,551
Think about it.

997
01:08:36,724 --> 01:08:37,971
[chuckles]

998
01:08:42,737 --> 01:08:44,205
Good night, didi.

999
01:08:48,625 --> 01:08:50,169
Good night.

1000
01:08:50,332 --> 01:08:54,668
CHINTAN: <i>That photograph
that you had sent...</i>

1001
01:08:54,840 --> 01:08:57,343
<i>you look very nice in it.</i>

1002
01:08:57,516 --> 01:08:59,232
You look very nice.

1003
01:08:59,386 --> 01:09:00,891
Thank you.

1004
01:09:04,066 --> 01:09:05,945
So, you like it here?

1005
01:09:06,109 --> 01:09:07,816
In Mumbai?

1006
01:09:09,619 --> 01:09:11,671
Yeah.

1007
01:09:11,825 --> 01:09:13,829
I miss it, too, sometimes.

1008
01:09:15,297 --> 01:09:16,889
But...
[sighs]

1009
01:09:17,041 --> 01:09:20,131
I feel like, uh... I feel
like I could live anywhere.

1010
01:09:20,302 --> 01:09:22,307
I-I could be happy anywhere.

1011
01:09:24,389 --> 01:09:25,682
But to be honest, uh,

1012
01:09:25,855 --> 01:09:27,860
I'd like to live away
from my parents.

1013
01:09:28,024 --> 01:09:29,691
[both laugh]

1014
01:09:32,905 --> 01:09:35,571
My dad told me you finished
first in the CA Foundation exam.

1015
01:09:35,744 --> 01:09:37,747
- Mm.
- Wow.

1016
01:09:37,920 --> 01:09:39,838
Oh, please, have it.

1017
01:09:41,881 --> 01:09:44,135
I'm watching my weight, so...

1018
01:09:52,651 --> 01:09:54,992
Where would you like to live?

1019
01:09:55,154 --> 01:09:56,708
You know, here or...

1020
01:10:02,251 --> 01:10:04,131
In a village.

1021
01:10:06,088 --> 01:10:08,216
In a village?

1022
01:10:08,389 --> 01:10:10,432
What would you do in a village?

1023
01:10:10,595 --> 01:10:13,309
I'd farm in the morning

1024
01:10:13,481 --> 01:10:16,819
and nap in the afternoon

1025
01:10:16,982 --> 01:10:18,526
under a tree.

1026
01:10:18,699 --> 01:10:20,243
[chuckles]

1027
01:10:35,184 --> 01:10:37,937
GROUP:
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

1028
01:10:38,100 --> 01:10:40,891
♪ Happy birthday, dear... ♪

1029
01:10:41,064 --> 01:10:42,818
[singing fades]

1030
01:10:42,991 --> 01:10:44,833
♪ ♪

1031
01:10:57,549 --> 01:11:00,551
[clapping, cheering]

1032
01:11:11,743 --> 01:11:13,201
- I have to go.
- Hmm?

1033
01:11:13,374 --> 01:11:14,841
I have a class.

1034
01:11:15,004 --> 01:11:16,845
Oh, uh, already?

1035
01:11:19,636 --> 01:11:21,477
Let me drop you?

1036
01:11:22,811 --> 01:11:24,355
Thank you.

1037
01:11:26,522 --> 01:11:28,364
Nice to meet you.

1038
01:11:30,905 --> 01:11:32,746
♪ ♪

1039
01:11:46,892 --> 01:11:49,855
- How was the birthday party?
- Good.

1040
01:11:52,647 --> 01:11:56,146
How could she reject him
after meeting just once?

1041
01:11:56,319 --> 01:11:58,199
She's right.

1042
01:11:58,371 --> 01:12:00,376
It's a tendency.

1043
01:12:00,540 --> 01:12:03,340
What if he puts on
all the weight again?

1044
01:12:03,503 --> 01:12:05,219
You seem very happy about it.

1045
01:12:06,466 --> 01:12:07,808
Who's happy?

1046
01:12:11,932 --> 01:12:14,560
[traffic rumbling,
horns honking]

1047
01:12:33,012 --> 01:12:34,854
Rafi miyan,

1048
01:12:35,017 --> 01:12:37,731
I've been considering shutting
down this kulfi business.

1049
01:12:37,894 --> 01:12:41,481
And getting a softie machine
instead.

1050
01:12:41,653 --> 01:12:44,789
You know what a softie is?
It's made with a machine.

1051
01:12:44,953 --> 01:12:48,214
So soft, it melts in your mouth.

1052
01:12:49,287 --> 01:12:50,658
[chuckles]

1053
01:12:51,713 --> 01:12:53,555
♪ ♪

1054
01:13:02,809 --> 01:13:05,149
Hello, uncle!

1055
01:13:05,322 --> 01:13:08,075
- Rafi miyan!
- Can I have a razor blade?

1056
01:13:14,711 --> 01:13:15,881
Is that all?

1057
01:13:16,045 --> 01:13:17,540
And soap.

1058
01:13:26,440 --> 01:13:27,735
And a comb, too.

1059
01:13:35,705 --> 01:13:37,958
Razor, soap, comb.

1060
01:13:42,428 --> 01:13:43,760
How much?

1061
01:13:43,924 --> 01:13:45,929
We'll settle up later.
Don't worry.

1062
01:13:53,150 --> 01:13:54,397
Uncle?

1063
01:13:55,701 --> 01:13:57,580
Do you remember Campa Cola?

1064
01:13:57,744 --> 01:13:58,703
Huh?

1065
01:13:58,741 --> 01:14:01,244
Campa? Why?

1066
01:14:01,417 --> 01:14:03,047
They must still sell it
somewhere?

1067
01:14:03,210 --> 01:14:07,056
They stopped making Campa
when my beard was still black.

1068
01:14:07,219 --> 01:14:09,310
A friend of mine wants some.

1069
01:14:09,472 --> 01:14:13,520
He can pay a good price.
Not too much.

1070
01:14:13,683 --> 01:14:16,810
You won't find it anywhere.

1071
01:14:16,982 --> 01:14:18,728
Can we ask someone?

1072
01:14:21,863 --> 01:14:24,577
What's that fragrance?

1073
01:14:24,750 --> 01:14:27,887
It's the magic
of Rafi's new cream!

1074
01:14:28,049 --> 01:14:30,140
Instant fairness in two weeks.

1075
01:14:30,303 --> 01:14:33,430
This is all Dadi's doing.
What do you say, Dadi?

1076
01:14:33,593 --> 01:14:36,259
Who listens to me anymore?

1077
01:14:36,432 --> 01:14:39,557
Dadi, I think
the new cream is working.

1078
01:14:39,730 --> 01:14:42,857
Rafi is glowing in the dark
like a firefly.

1079
01:14:43,029 --> 01:14:44,621
[light laughter]

1080
01:14:54,921 --> 01:14:57,674
Should I bring Noorie
to the Gateway this evening?

1081
01:14:57,847 --> 01:15:00,234
Why should I be a bone
in your kebab?

1082
01:15:03,275 --> 01:15:06,075
Who said
you're a bone in my kebab?

1083
01:15:06,239 --> 01:15:10,544
I'm going to Nalasopara
to see Zohra again.

1084
01:15:10,698 --> 01:15:12,117
Understood?

1085
01:15:13,709 --> 01:15:15,713
Is everything all right?

1086
01:15:15,877 --> 01:15:17,881
Everything's fine, son.

1087
01:15:21,305 --> 01:15:23,645
What could be wrong?

1088
01:15:36,123 --> 01:15:37,254
I'm going.

1089
01:15:37,416 --> 01:15:38,673
Go, go.

1090
01:15:49,433 --> 01:15:50,393
I'm going.

1091
01:15:50,566 --> 01:15:51,524
Go.

1092
01:15:52,647 --> 01:15:53,605
Go.

1093
01:15:59,532 --> 01:16:01,037
- Should I go?
- Just go!

1094
01:16:01,210 --> 01:16:02,544
I'm going.

1095
01:16:02,707 --> 01:16:05,334
Those were the days.

1096
01:16:05,507 --> 01:16:07,137
Campa flew off the shelves.

1097
01:16:08,883 --> 01:16:11,050
Now it's gone forever.

1098
01:16:11,223 --> 01:16:13,180
Gafoor bhai told me

1099
01:16:13,352 --> 01:16:15,184
you'd know where I can find it.

1100
01:16:21,369 --> 01:16:25,168
It's been years since anyone
came looking for Campa Cola.

1101
01:16:25,330 --> 01:16:27,910
You're the first.

1102
01:16:28,083 --> 01:16:30,624
There must be a Campa factory
somewhere.

1103
01:16:32,427 --> 01:16:34,480
It's a big country.

1104
01:16:34,642 --> 01:16:36,186
Correct.

1105
01:16:36,350 --> 01:16:37,894
The country is big.

1106
01:16:50,370 --> 01:16:52,586
But the country's memory
is very small.

1107
01:17:11,949 --> 01:17:13,954
[clicks tongue, sighs]

1108
01:17:16,380 --> 01:17:18,759
Many years ago, a man came here,
just like you,

1109
01:17:18,921 --> 01:17:20,801
a Parsi gentleman.

1110
01:17:20,973 --> 01:17:23,438
His wife loved Campa Cola.

1111
01:17:23,601 --> 01:17:25,357
When the factories
started closing down,

1112
01:17:25,519 --> 01:17:27,524
he bought the Campa Cola formula

1113
01:17:27,688 --> 01:17:29,816
and set up a factory
in his house

1114
01:17:29,989 --> 01:17:32,291
so his wife
could keep having Campa.

1115
01:17:32,444 --> 01:17:35,782
He must still make it, right?

1116
01:17:35,955 --> 01:17:37,671
I don't know.

1117
01:17:37,834 --> 01:17:40,673
I don't know
if he's dead or still alive.

1118
01:17:40,836 --> 01:17:42,629
Do you know his name?

1119
01:17:42,802 --> 01:17:44,269
Soda Bottle...

1120
01:17:44,422 --> 01:17:48,057
- Mr. Sodabottlewallah.
- Mr. Sodabottlewallah?

1121
01:17:48,229 --> 01:17:50,234
Do you have an address?

1122
01:17:52,565 --> 01:17:55,279
[man sighs]

1123
01:17:55,442 --> 01:17:59,153
Your friend must like
Campa Cola a lot...

1124
01:17:59,326 --> 01:18:01,369
Is it a special friend?

1125
01:18:01,542 --> 01:18:02,837
[horn honking]

1126
01:18:02,999 --> 01:18:04,831
Miloni. Miloni.

1127
01:18:08,092 --> 01:18:09,799
- Everything okay?
- Yes, sir.

1128
01:18:09,971 --> 01:18:11,305
Yeah?

1129
01:18:11,476 --> 01:18:13,232
Can I drop you somewhere?

1130
01:18:13,395 --> 01:18:15,323
- No, thank you, sir.
- I can drop you, no problem.

1131
01:18:15,485 --> 01:18:17,295
- No, it's okay, sir. I'm fine.
- Wait one second.

1132
01:18:17,317 --> 01:18:18,775
One second.

1133
01:18:18,948 --> 01:18:20,329
[door opens]

1134
01:18:26,084 --> 01:18:27,464
[door closes]

1135
01:18:34,014 --> 01:18:36,777
Shall we go for coffee?
Or one tea?

1136
01:18:39,193 --> 01:18:41,160
Sir, I'm getting late.

1137
01:18:41,323 --> 01:18:43,662
I still have that photo
you gave me.

1138
01:18:46,789 --> 01:18:49,215
Come.

1139
01:18:49,369 --> 01:18:52,207
One quick coffee.

1140
01:18:52,380 --> 01:18:54,931
Come now.
I know a place just here.

1141
01:18:55,094 --> 01:18:56,590
Around the way.
It'll take five minutes.

1142
01:18:56,677 --> 01:18:58,383
Sir, I have to go home.
I'm getting late.

1143
01:18:58,556 --> 01:19:00,311
Everyone has five minutes.

1144
01:19:00,474 --> 01:19:01,769
Come. Yes.

1145
01:19:01,932 --> 01:19:03,975
- [car door opens]
- RAFI: Madam?

1146
01:19:04,148 --> 01:19:05,184
Everything okay?

1147
01:19:05,357 --> 01:19:07,312
Yes, man, of course it's okay.

1148
01:19:09,989 --> 01:19:11,868
This is my student.

1149
01:19:12,041 --> 01:19:14,045
I'm a teacher.

1150
01:19:14,208 --> 01:19:15,417
Off you go!

1151
01:19:17,335 --> 01:19:18,629
Go now!

1152
01:19:21,554 --> 01:19:23,770
Miloni. Miloni.

1153
01:19:23,933 --> 01:19:26,934
- One second, one second.
- Sorry, sir. I have to go.

1154
01:19:31,279 --> 01:19:32,736
- You okay?
- Yes.

1155
01:19:45,885 --> 01:19:47,381
I'm okay, too.

1156
01:19:55,859 --> 01:19:57,691
That guy's your teacher?

1157
01:19:59,743 --> 01:20:01,413
How can he...?

1158
01:20:03,206 --> 01:20:05,171
He shouldn't have grabbed
your hand like that.

1159
01:20:15,769 --> 01:20:19,106
When I got out,
I felt like doing something,

1160
01:20:19,279 --> 01:20:20,823
but I couldn't.

1161
01:20:39,486 --> 01:20:41,327
♪ ♪

1162
01:20:46,870 --> 01:20:48,338
Where to, sir?

1163
01:20:52,672 --> 01:20:54,054
Sir, where to?

1164
01:21:01,563 --> 01:21:03,404
♪ ♪

1165
01:21:12,036 --> 01:21:13,954
[rain pattering]

1166
01:21:30,613 --> 01:21:32,416
♪ ♪

1167
01:21:51,691 --> 01:21:53,486
♪ ♪

1168
01:22:05,886 --> 01:22:07,727
♪ ♪

1169
01:22:42,358 --> 01:22:45,149
[song playing in Hindi]

1170
01:22:54,462 --> 01:22:58,097
♪ Oh, Noorie ♪

1171
01:22:58,259 --> 01:23:00,973
♪ Noorie ♪

1172
01:23:01,146 --> 01:23:02,988
♪ ♪

1173
01:23:12,540 --> 01:23:14,343
[song continues in Hindi]

1174
01:23:52,695 --> 01:23:54,488
♪ ♪

1175
01:24:15,730 --> 01:24:17,523
♪ ♪

1176
01:24:39,563 --> 01:24:42,277
[footfalls on stairs,
trapdoor creaks open]

1177
01:24:52,922 --> 01:24:54,341
They're hot and fresh!

1178
01:25:09,370 --> 01:25:11,163
♪ ♪

1179
01:25:11,326 --> 01:25:13,158
[train passing outside]

1180
01:25:28,483 --> 01:25:30,286
♪ ♪

1181
01:25:45,890 --> 01:25:47,683
[footsteps approaching]

1182
01:25:50,609 --> 01:25:52,153
Anything else, didi?

1183
01:25:55,365 --> 01:25:57,159
Good night, didi.

1184
01:25:58,453 --> 01:26:00,046
Good night.

1185
01:26:01,666 --> 01:26:03,469
[footsteps departing]

1186
01:26:06,212 --> 01:26:08,465
[train rattling in distance]

1187
01:26:12,100 --> 01:26:14,939
[floorboards creaking]

1188
01:26:21,490 --> 01:26:24,329
[footsteps approaching]

1189
01:26:32,384 --> 01:26:34,426
She hasn't slept a wink either.

1190
01:26:40,862 --> 01:26:42,118
Tiwari?

1191
01:26:44,862 --> 01:26:47,029
Are you Tiwari?

1192
01:26:47,202 --> 01:26:48,870
Do you smoke bidi?

1193
01:26:53,004 --> 01:26:54,461
Can I have one?

1194
01:27:04,982 --> 01:27:06,602
[door opens]

1195
01:27:06,775 --> 01:27:08,905
[train horn blowing
in distance]

1196
01:27:21,928 --> 01:27:23,348
Do you miss it?

1197
01:27:23,520 --> 01:27:24,777
Smoking bidi?

1198
01:27:27,941 --> 01:27:29,035
No.

1199
01:27:30,281 --> 01:27:31,825
I don't miss bidi.

1200
01:27:37,628 --> 01:27:39,172
Why did you kill yourself?

1201
01:27:41,463 --> 01:27:44,053
I woke up to pee one night,

1202
01:27:44,216 --> 01:27:46,969
thought about hanging myself,
and so I did.

1203
01:27:48,014 --> 01:27:49,722
Why?

1204
01:27:49,894 --> 01:27:51,015
There was someone...

1205
01:27:51,188 --> 01:27:52,272
Who?

1206
01:27:52,444 --> 01:27:53,702
A girl.

1207
01:27:58,822 --> 01:28:01,873
What was your trade
when you were alive?

1208
01:28:06,965 --> 01:28:08,547
I was a farmer back
in the village,

1209
01:28:08,719 --> 01:28:10,436
and here I did anything
I could find.

1210
01:28:16,229 --> 01:28:18,818
I'm a photographer.
At the Gateway.

1211
01:28:20,909 --> 01:28:22,453
Do you get by?

1212
01:28:23,288 --> 01:28:25,714
Yeah, sort of.

1213
01:28:27,498 --> 01:28:28,831
It's okay.

1214
01:28:31,257 --> 01:28:33,089
[sighs]

1215
01:28:34,345 --> 01:28:36,973
But I won't do it for long now.

1216
01:28:38,901 --> 01:28:41,068
I'm thinking
of starting my own business.

1217
01:28:46,037 --> 01:28:47,503
You know Campa Cola?

1218
01:28:49,661 --> 01:28:51,829
Mm.

1219
01:28:52,001 --> 01:28:54,419
I'm thinking of starting
a Campa Cola factory.

1220
01:29:02,148 --> 01:29:04,277
♪ ♪

1221
01:29:04,440 --> 01:29:06,109
Should I?

1222
01:29:06,282 --> 01:29:07,489
Why not?

1223
01:29:24,062 --> 01:29:26,229
♪ ♪

1224
01:29:35,916 --> 01:29:38,717
[footsteps passing,
jewelry jingling]

1225
01:29:51,481 --> 01:29:53,313
♪ ♪

1226
01:30:14,518 --> 01:30:17,692
I've fixed up all
of your shirts.

1227
01:30:19,322 --> 01:30:20,741
Don't you have
to go meet Zohra again?

1228
01:30:20,866 --> 01:30:22,544
No.

1229
01:30:24,165 --> 01:30:25,709
Listen,

1230
01:30:25,873 --> 01:30:28,165
I want to talk to you
about something important.

1231
01:30:28,338 --> 01:30:29,804
Sit down.

1232
01:30:32,049 --> 01:30:33,046
Right here.

1233
01:30:35,098 --> 01:30:37,678
Hmm...
[speaks Hindi]

1234
01:30:40,104 --> 01:30:42,818
I'm your grandmother.

1235
01:30:42,991 --> 01:30:44,535
Not a child.

1236
01:30:44,698 --> 01:30:47,786
Nothing gets past me.

1237
01:30:47,950 --> 01:30:49,829
That girl,

1238
01:30:50,002 --> 01:30:53,550
she's not from our religion.

1239
01:30:56,513 --> 01:31:00,148
And her name isn't Noorie,
but something else...

1240
01:31:00,312 --> 01:31:01,980
The other day,

1241
01:31:02,143 --> 01:31:04,100
I saw her on a big poster.

1242
01:31:04,272 --> 01:31:05,769
Have you seen it?

1243
01:31:07,821 --> 01:31:10,362
I was very angry that day.

1244
01:31:10,535 --> 01:31:12,702
I felt very bad.

1245
01:31:12,875 --> 01:31:15,004
But I went back again
the next day.

1246
01:31:15,167 --> 01:31:16,586
They'd changed the billboard.

1247
01:31:16,750 --> 01:31:20,298
And you know
what they'd put up instead?

1248
01:31:20,471 --> 01:31:25,400
It was an ad
for Home Loans instead.

1249
01:31:25,563 --> 01:31:28,152
With a mother, father,
and two children.

1250
01:31:29,399 --> 01:31:30,819
Hmm?

1251
01:31:30,991 --> 01:31:33,954
For years now,

1252
01:31:34,117 --> 01:31:36,237
I've watched you toil

1253
01:31:36,409 --> 01:31:38,664
and try to pay back
your father's debts.

1254
01:31:38,836 --> 01:31:41,464
For what are you struggling,
day and night?

1255
01:31:44,302 --> 01:31:45,895
Dadi, I'll repay the debt

1256
01:31:46,058 --> 01:31:49,193
and get our house back for you.

1257
01:31:49,357 --> 01:31:51,773
Stop this nonsense!

1258
01:31:51,936 --> 01:31:56,195
I remember the hard times too,
son.

1259
01:31:56,367 --> 01:31:59,878
I raised all of you by myself.

1260
01:32:00,040 --> 01:32:02,045
All three of you.

1261
01:32:02,208 --> 01:32:05,709
Did you just cry
all the time then?

1262
01:32:05,881 --> 01:32:08,048
Did we never laugh?

1263
01:32:09,977 --> 01:32:14,646
Then stop wearing those years
like a medal!

1264
01:32:14,810 --> 01:32:16,728
Forget about it, son.

1265
01:32:16,901 --> 01:32:19,288
Forget those days.
Forget that house.

1266
01:32:19,442 --> 01:32:22,031
Forget all those people.
Forever.

1267
01:32:22,204 --> 01:32:23,672
Hmm?

1268
01:32:25,292 --> 01:32:26,375
Understood.

1269
01:32:26,539 --> 01:32:28,332
What do you understand?

1270
01:32:28,505 --> 01:32:29,675
I said I understand!

1271
01:32:29,838 --> 01:32:31,382
Don't you shout!

1272
01:32:32,638 --> 01:32:34,892
I have a mother's heart, son.

1273
01:32:41,030 --> 01:32:43,446
♪ ♪

1274
01:32:57,007 --> 01:32:59,425
[machinery clanking
and whirring]

1275
01:33:02,186 --> 01:33:04,018
[glass clinking]

1276
01:33:13,167 --> 01:33:14,711
[doorbell ringing]

1277
01:33:16,045 --> 01:33:17,962
[clanking and whirring
continue]

1278
01:33:26,268 --> 01:33:28,100
[knocking]

1279
01:33:38,246 --> 01:33:40,002
[clanking and whirring
continue]

1280
01:33:47,348 --> 01:33:49,017
[clanking and whirring stop]

1281
01:33:59,624 --> 01:34:01,628
[doorbell ringing]

1282
01:34:04,131 --> 01:34:05,924
[birds cawing outside]

1283
01:34:25,834 --> 01:34:27,628
♪ ♪

1284
01:34:27,791 --> 01:34:29,958
[machinery rumbles and creaks]

1285
01:34:30,130 --> 01:34:31,923
[machinery whirring,
glass clinking]

1286
01:34:52,006 --> 01:34:53,799
♪ ♪

1287
01:35:13,086 --> 01:35:14,928
♪ ♪

1288
01:35:25,228 --> 01:35:27,356
[machinery rattling,
bottles clinking]

1289
01:35:38,165 --> 01:35:40,169
[machinery stops]

1290
01:35:52,186 --> 01:35:55,188
For your special friend.
Serve chilled.

1291
01:35:55,361 --> 01:35:57,777
Thank you, sir.

1292
01:36:00,118 --> 01:36:01,412
WOMAN:
Excuse me.

1293
01:36:01,584 --> 01:36:03,340
Is that you up on the billboard?

1294
01:36:10,848 --> 01:36:11,817
No.

1295
01:36:18,358 --> 01:36:21,408
<i>[song playing in Hindi]</i>

1296
01:36:25,292 --> 01:36:27,345
[song continues,
projector rattling]

1297
01:36:30,260 --> 01:36:32,053
Just a rat scuttling
over your feet.

1298
01:36:32,216 --> 01:36:34,048
It's gone now.

1299
01:36:34,221 --> 01:36:35,468
Don't worry.

1300
01:36:51,340 --> 01:36:53,133
♪ ♪

1301
01:37:02,023 --> 01:37:04,277
- [song stops]
- [laughter in distance]

1302
01:37:04,440 --> 01:37:06,396
[projector rattling]

1303
01:37:36,539 --> 01:37:38,044
Are you all right?

1304
01:37:38,208 --> 01:37:40,001
I'm all right here.

1305
01:37:44,759 --> 01:37:46,714
They have good samosas here.

1306
01:37:54,444 --> 01:37:56,065
You're missing your movie.

1307
01:37:59,038 --> 01:38:01,129
I know the rest of the story.

1308
01:38:02,999 --> 01:38:04,620
You've seen it before?

1309
01:38:04,792 --> 01:38:05,876
No.

1310
01:38:13,731 --> 01:38:16,445
After this song,

1311
01:38:16,608 --> 01:38:19,610
the boy and girl fall in love.

1312
01:38:19,782 --> 01:38:22,918
And then the girl's parents
will object.

1313
01:38:25,661 --> 01:38:27,167
The boy's a...

1314
01:38:28,798 --> 01:38:30,975
He's an ordinary motor mechanic,
so...

1315
01:38:39,817 --> 01:38:43,202
The stories are all the same
in movies these days.

1316
01:38:43,365 --> 01:38:44,785
The same.

1317
01:38:53,214 --> 01:38:54,308
Shall we go?

1318
01:38:54,461 --> 01:38:55,842
Yes, let's.

1319
01:39:04,646 --> 01:39:06,440
♪ ♪

